You called it. The active key id radio was still pointing at
key_2024Q4_b. Just flipped to key_2026Q1_a and the signatures
validate again — 401 rate dropped to zero.

Thank you for the fast turnaround. Two follow-up asks:

  - Could you add an alert / inline warning when the active key id
    differs from the most-recently-saved secret? This would have
    saved us about three hours.
  - Is there a programmatic key-rotation endpoint we could call from
    our deploy pipeline so we never touch the UI for this?

Casey

